+	//
+	// Solution: Apply penalty every frame with frame-rate compensation
+	//   - Use pow(flRatio, flFrametimeRatio) to adjust penalty strength
+	//   - 100fps: pow(0.75, 1.0) = 0.75 per frame
+	//   - 600fps: pow(0.75, 0.166) ≈ 0.952 per frame
+	//   - After 6 frames at 600fps: 0.952^6 ≈ 0.75 (same as 100fps!)
+	//
+	// Why this is perfect:
+	//   - Every frame applies penalty (no sudden changes)
+	//   - Penalty strength adjusted by frame rate (all FPS identical)
+	//   - No "forward push" feeling (smooth speed changes)
